    "docs/LOCKFILE.md": "LOCKFILE POLICY (npm + package-lock.json)\n\nGoal\n- Reproducible installs across dev/CI/prod by committing package-lock.json.\n\nStandard\n- Use npm for this repo.\n- Commit package-lock.json for every dependency change.\n- CI/deploy uses `npm ci`.\n\nWhy package-lock.json matters\n- `package.json` expresses version ranges. Without a lockfile, your installed versions can differ between machines and over time.\n- `package-lock.json` pins the entire dependency tree (direct + transitive) and includes integrity hashes.\n\nTeam workflow\n\n1) Install exactly what's locked (most common)\n- `npm ci`\n  - Uses package-lock.json exclusively.\n  - Produces consistent installs.\n  - Fails if package.json and package-lock.json are out of sync.\n\n2) Add/remove a dependency\n- Add: `npm install <pkg>` or `npm install -D <pkg>`\n- Remove: `npm uninstall <pkg>`\n- Commit changes to both `package.json` and `package-lock.json`.\n\n3) Update dependencies (intentional)\n\nA) Update transitive deps within current ranges\n- `npm update`\n\nB) Bump a direct dependency\n- `npm install <pkg>@<version>`\n\n4) Generate/refresh the lockfile\n- `npm run lock:generate`\n  - Creates/updates package-lock.json without installing node_modules.\n  - Use when bootstrapping, after deleting lockfile, or after standardizing npm versions.\n\nCI / Deployment pipeline\n- Required: `npm ci`\n- Do not use `npm install` in CI.\n- Ensure the lockfile is present and committed.\n- Optionally enforce: `npm run lock:verify`.\n\nVersion alignment\n- Different npm major versions can rewrite lockfile metadata/format.\n- Align Node + npm via tooling (Volta/nvm/asdf) and/or `package.json#engines`.\n\nRecommended files\n\npackage.json\n- Add `engines`:\n  - \"node\": \">=20 <21\" (example)\n  - \"npm\": \">=10 <11\" (example)\n\n.npmrc\n- package-lock=true\n- engine-strict=true\n\nCommands\n- `npm run lock:ci-install`\n- `npm run lock:verify`\n- `npm run lock:update`\n- `npm run lock:generate`\n"
